OL,1,D]S737{kkkc5FSalman Rushdie: Losing an  
OL,2,D]S555{jjj25Feye upsets me every day    
OL,3,D]Suuu{rrzq5F                           
OL,4,T#######################################
OL,5, Sir Salman Rushdie has spoken in       
OL,6, chilling detail to the BBC about what  
OL,7, he remembers of the attack two years   
OL,8, ago, in which he was stabbed on stage. 
OL,10,FThe Booker Prize-winning author said   
OL,11,Fhis eye was left hanging down his face 
OL,12,F"like a soft-boiled egg", and that     
OL,13,Flosing the eye "upsets him every day". 
OL,15,F"I remember thinking I was dying," he  
OL,16,Fsaid. "Fortunately, I was wrong."      
OL,18,FSir Salman said he is using his new    
OL,19,Fbook, Knife, as a way of fighting back 
OL,20,Fagainst what happened.                 
